
Amsterdam, 13 July 1781. RC and signature in John Thaxters hand PCC, No. 84, III, f. 287288. LbCAdams Papers. printed:JA, Corr. in the Boston Patriot, p. 544546.
John Thaxter wrote this letter during John Adams absence at Paris. It provided an English translation of a placard issued by the States of Utrecht on 4 July. The placard deplored the publication of scandalous reflexions and malicious insinuations against the Duke of Brunswick-Wolfenbttel and declared that henceforth anyone who composed, printed, or distributed such materials would be fined one thousand florins.
